## Known Pitfalls & Gotchas

### `"use server"` Double-Labeling Trap
Both the file-level `'use server'` and the function-level `'use server'` can coexist, but **only one is needed**. If both are present on the same module, the file-level directive covers everything. A common mistake is putting `'use server'` on both the file and individual functions, which can cause "stream already consumed" runtime errors when the actions are imported elsewhere. **Best practice**: Use file-level `'use server'` in `app/actions.ts` and omit it from individual exported functions.

### GitHub Actions — Vercel Deployment Action Version
The community action `amondnet/vercel-action@v25` has been unmaintained since ~2022. Use **`vercel/vercel-action@v38` or newer** — it is officially maintained by Vercel. The older action may silently fail on newer Node.js versions used in GitHub Actions runners.

### Optimizer Version Recommendations — Verify Before Applying
The Meta-Brain Optimizer may recommend version upgrades (e.g., `v25 → v38`) for GitHub Actions that are **not actually present** in the target workflow file. Always grep for the exact string in the file before suggesting a version bump. False-positive recommendations create spurious diffs and waste audit cycles.

### Vercel AI SDK Version — 4.x May Be Outdated
The Vercel AI SDK version listed here (4.x) may have been superseded by 5.x as of 2026-03-21. ⚠ Verify via `npm info ai` or the [Vercel AI SDK releases page](https://github.com/vercel/ai/releases) before trusting this version number.

### `proxy.ts` Matcher Excludes Server Functions
A `proxy.ts` matcher that excludes a path will also skip Server Function calls on that path. Authentication in `proxy.ts` does **not** cover Server Function authorization — always verify auth inside each Server Function body, not just in the proxy layer.

### React Compiler + Manual Memoization
Do not add manual `useMemo` or `useCallback` calls in components when React Compiler is enabled — the compiler handles this automatically. In some cases, manual memoization can disable compiler optimizations on the same component.

### React Compiler Config — Verify Stable vs Experimental
The `experimental.reactCompiler: true` config key implies React Compiler is experimental. If v1.0 is officially stable, the correct config key is `compiler: { reactCompiler: true }`. ⚠ Always verify the correct config key for your installed Next.js version by running `npx next info` or checking the official Next.js configuration docs.

### `generateMetadata` — params is a Promise in Next.js 15+
The legacy `params: { slug: string }` signature is deprecated. Always use `params: Promise<{ slug: string }>` and `await` it inside the function body. Failing to await params causes a runtime error in Next.js 15+.

